		  spacelike components of the third-order
		  mass--momentum--energy density-flux four-tensor. The
		  corresponding Galilean transformation rules of the physical
		  quantities are derived. It is proved that the
		  non-equilibrium thermodynamic frame theory, including the
		  thermostatic Gibbs relation and extensivity condition and
		  also the entropy production, is independent of the
		  reference frame and also the flow-frame of the fluid. The
		  continuity-Fourier--Navier--Stokes equations are obtained
		  almost in the traditional form if the flow of the fluid is
		  fixed to the temperature. This choice of the flow-frame is
		  the thermo-flow. A simple consequence of the theory is that
		  the relation between the total, kinetic and internal
		  energies is a Galilean transformation rule.",
